        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:12PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 212 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Shoals, or 21 miles northeast of Petersburg,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shoals, Loogootee, Montgomery, Cannelburg, Alfordsville, and Lacy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
